      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 29
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 1997 Porsche 911 Carrera (993), the definitive final chapter of the air-cooled era. This specimen features the 3.6L M64/21 flat-six engine equipped with the Varioram induction system, ensuring optimized volumetric efficiency across the power band. The drivetrain is anchored by the coveted G50 6-speed manual transaxle and a factory-optioned limited-slip differential. Mechanically, the vehicle is impeccable: the crankcase and cylinder heads are bone dry, with no evidence of weeping at the chain covers. The suspension geometry remains precise, upgraded with Bilstein B6 dampers and M030-spec anti-roll bars for neutral cornering. The exterior displays factory-original paint depth across all panels, while the interior remains free of UV-induced dash shrinkage or bolster compression. A turn-key example for the collector demanding mechanical perfection.",
